does not surprise Carver.\", \"from\": 1507, \"to\": 1556, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1549, \"end\": 1555, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/George_Washington_Carver\", \"score\": 0.8144801170727122, \"rank\": 0.2267627011054119, \"text\": \"Carver\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/George_Washington_Carver\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/George_Washington_Carver\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Wool uniforms\", \"from\": 1507, \"to\": 1520}, {\"ngram\": \"summer\", \"from\": 1524, \"to\": 1530}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She said people who have worked closely with sheep for generations, especially those near Shaniko, once deemed the \\\"Wool Capital of the World,\\\"know that the natural material is the original performance fiber and a premier fiber for year-round use.\", \"from\": 1557, \"to\": 1804, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1647, \"end\": 1654, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shaniko,_Oregon\", \"score\": 0.973303180980594, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Shaniko\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shaniko,_Oregon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shaniko,_Oregon\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"people\", \"from\": 1566, \"to\": 1572}, {\"ngram\": \"sheep\", \"from\": 1602, \"to\": 1607}, {\"ngram\": \"generations\", \"from\": 1612, \"to\": 1623}, {\"ngram\": \"especially those\", \"from\": 1625, \"to\": 1641}, {\"ngram\": \"the \\\"Wool Capital\", \"from\": 1668, \"to\": 1685}, {\"ngram\": \"the World,\\\"know\", \"from\": 1689, \"to\": 1704}, {\"ngram\": \"the natural material\", \"from\": 1710, \"to\": 1730}, {\"ngram\": \"the original performance fiber\", \"from\": 1734, \"to\": 1764}, {\"ngram\": \"a premier fiber\", \"from\": 1769, \"to\": 1784}, {\"ngram\": \"year-round use\", \"from\": 1789, \"to\": 1803}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Wool not only supports our 'life energy' in a way no other fiber does, it makes the best suiting fabric in the world,\\\" she said.\", \"from\": 1806, \"to\": 1935, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Wool\", \"from\": 1807, \"to\": 1811}, {\"ngram\": \"our 'life energy\", \"from\": 1830, \"to\": 1846}, {\"ngram\": \"a way\", \"from\": 1851, \"to\": 1856}, {\"ngram\": \"no other fiber\", \"from\": 1857, \"to\": 1871}, {\"ngram\": \"the best suiting fabric\", \"from\": 1887, \"to\": 1910}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 1914, \"to\": 1923}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Ralph Lauren company has been an official outfitter of Team USA nine times, and all apparel worn by U.S. athletes during official Olympic and Paralympic ceremonies is made in the United States.\", \"from\": 1937, \"to\": 2134, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1941, \"end\": 1953, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ralph_Lauren_Corporation\", \"score\": 0.9996891789576362, \"rank\": 0.0003109176822649396, \"text\": \"Ralph Lauren\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ralph_Lauren_Corporation\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ralph_Lauren_Corporation\"}, {\"begin\": 2120, \"end\": 2133, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999999372744262, \"rank\": 6.272399291388483e-08, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an official outfitter\", \"from\": 1971, \"to\": 1992}, {\"ngram\": \"Team USA\", \"from\": 1996, \"to\": 2004}, {\"ngram\": \"all apparel\", \"from\": 2021, \"to\": 2032}, {\"ngram\": \"U.S. athletes\", \"from\": 2041, \"to\": 2054}, {\"ngram\": \"official Olympic and Paralympic ceremonies\", \"from\": 2062, \"to\": 2104}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This year, Team USA members will wear a single-breasted navy blazer with red-and-white tipping along with a blue-and-white striped Oxford shirt, blue jeans and cream-colored suede buck lace-up shoes for the opening ceremony.\", \"from\": 2136, \"to\": 2360, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2147, \"end\": 2155, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999940975709731, \"rank\": 5.898628442229857e-06, \"text\": \"Team USA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 2267, \"end\": 2279, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dress_shirt\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Oxford shirt\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dress_shirt\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dress_shirt\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a single-breasted navy blazer\", \"from\": 2174, \"to\": 2203}, {\"ngram\": \"red-and-white tipping\", \"from\": 2209, \"to\": 2230}, {\"ngram\": \"blue jeans\", \"from\": 2281, \"to\": 2291}, {\"ngram\": \"cream-colored suede buck lace-up shoes\", \"from\": 2296, \"to\": 2334}, {\"ngram\": \"the opening ceremony\", \"from\": 2339, \"to\": 2359}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The company contacted Carver 16 months ago about its tailored blazers with these specific requirements: \\\"We had exactly what they needed,\\\" said Carver, whose family has been raising sheep, cattle, grains and hay on the Imperial Stock Ranch for 153 years.\", \"from\": 2362, \"to\": 2617, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2384, \"end\": 2390, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/George_Washington_Carver\", \"score\": 0.8144801170727122, \"rank\": 0.2267627011054119, \"text\": \"Carver\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/George_Washington_Carver\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/George_Washington_Carver\"}, {\"begin\": 2507, \"end\": 2513, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/George_Washington_Carver\", \"score\": 0.8144801170727122, \"rank\": 0.2267627011054119, \"text\": \"Carver\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/George_Washington_Carver\"